spirit:field.spirit:name: EN_A_FLAGS_B2A_OR
spirit:field.spirit:description: Enable A_FLAGS_B2A_OR bit: This bit controls whether or not the ORed version of the flag bits from processor B to processor A (A_FLAGS_B2A[31:0]) contributes to the INTERRUPT_A output or is masked. If set to 1, the ORed flag contribution is enabled, otherwise, if 0, the ORed flag contribution is masked. The default value of 0 disables (masks) the contribution of the ORed flags to the INTERRUPT_A output.

spirit:field.spirit:name: EN_DPWRB
spirit:field.spirit:description: Enable DPWRB bit: This bit controls whether or not the DPWRB bit of the INTSTATA register contributes to the INTERRUPT_A output or is masked. If set to 1, the DPWRB bit contribution is enabled, otherwise, if 0, the DPWRB bit is masked. The default value of 0 disables (masks) the contribution of the DPWRB bit to the INTERRUPT_A output.

spirit:field.spirit:name: EN_FULL_A2B
spirit:field.spirit:description: Enable FULL_A2B bit: This bit controls whether or not the FULL_A2B bit of the INTSTATA register contributes to the INTERRUPT_A output or is masked. If set to 1, the FULL_A2B bit contribution is enabled, otherwise, if 0, the FULL_A2B bit is masked. The default value of 0 disables (masks) the contribution of the FULL_A2B bit to the INTERRUPT_A output.

spirit:field.spirit:name: EN_MSG_B2A
spirit:field.spirit:description: Enable MSG_B2A bit: This bit controls whether or not the MSG_B2A bit of the INTSTATA register contributes to the INTERRUPT_A output or is masked. If set to 1, the MSB_B2A bit contribution is enabled, otherwise, if 0, the MSG_B2A bit is masked. The default value of 0 disables (masks) the contribution of the MSG_B2A bit to the INTERRUPT_A output.

spirit:field.spirit:name: A_FLAGS_B2A_OR
spirit:field.spirit:description: ORed flag bits from processor B to processor A: If set to 1, this bit indicates that processor B has set one or more general purpose flags in the A_FLAGS_B2A[31:0] register to indicate to processor A that it must take some action followed by clearing of these general purpose flags; this action that must be taken by processor A is entirely application specific. This bit will not be cleared when reading this register, but rather when all bits of the A_FLAGS_B2A[31:0] register are cleared. If MSG_B2A_FLAGS=0, this bit will be permanently tied to logic 0.

spirit:field.spirit:name: DPWRB
spirit:field.spirit:description: Processor B has written to dual-port SRAM: If set to 1, this bit indicates that processor B has written data into the B port of the dual-port SRAM. This bit will be cleared when reading this register. If USE_FIFOS=1, this bit will be permanently tied to logic 0.

spirit:field.spirit:name: FULL_A2B
spirit:field.spirit:description: FIFO A->B is full: If set to 1, this bit indicates that the A->B FIFO (from processor A to processor B) is full. This bit will be cleared when at least one message has been read from the A->B FIFO by the B processor. If USE_FIFOS=0, this bit will be permanently tied to logic 0.

spirit:field.spirit:name: MSG_B2A
spirit:field.spirit:description: Message(s) available in FIFO B->A: If set to 1, this bit indicates that at least one message is available in the B->A FIFO (from processor B to processor A). This bit will be cleared when all messages have been read from the B->A FIFO. If USE_FIFOS=0, this bit will be permanently tied to logic 0.

spirit:register.spirit:name: A_FLAGS_B2A

spirit:field.spirit:name: FLAGS
spirit:field.spirit:description: Message flag bits from processor B to processor A: These 32 possible flag logic bits can be used to send interrupts from processor B to processor A. Processor A can clear any of the 32 bits by writing a logic 1 in that bit position, for example, if the A_FLAGS_B2A[31:0] register value contains 0xFFAA0000 and processor A writes the value 0xFF000000 to this register, the value will be changed to 0x00AA0000 on subsequent reads since writing logic 0 values to any of the bits is ignored.

spirit:register.spirit:description: 32 possible flag logic bits that can be used to send interrupts from processor B to processor A (read-able and clear-able from processor A).

spirit:register.spirit:name: A_FLAGS_A2B

spirit:field.spirit:name: FLAGS
spirit:field.spirit:description: Message flag bits from processor A to processor B: These 32 possible flag logic bits can be used to send interrupts from processor A to processor B. Processor A can set any of the 32 bits by writing a logic 1 in that bit position, for example, if the A_FLAGS_A2B[31:0] register value contains 0x00550000 and processor A writes the value 0xAA000000 to this register, the value will be changed to 0xAA550000 on subsequent reads; writing logic 0 values to any of the bits is ignored.

spirit:register.spirit:description: 32 possible flag logic bits that can be used to send interrupts from processor A to processor B (read-able and set-able from processor A).

spirit:register.spirit:name: INITWADDR

spirit:field.spirit:name: INITADDR
spirit:field.spirit:description: Init/Config write address: If the parameter USE_INIT=1, this register is connected to the INITADDR outputs. Note that the actual width of this register will be determined by the INITWIDTH parameter and can range from 1 to 16 bits; unused bits will return 0 when read, and will be ignored if processor A writes to them. If the Init/config interface is used (USE_INIT=1), processor A should first write the starting address for the INITADDR outputs to this register, followed by subsequent writes to the INITWDATA register after which the contents of this register will be automatically incremented by 1; in this manner, the Init/Config interface can be initialized in a connected instance of CoreABC operating in soft mode. If the parameter USE_INIT=0, these bits are permanently tied to logic 0 and writes to it have no effect (also, the INITADDR outputs will be tied to logic 0).

spirit:register.spirit:description: INITCFG indirect address register - the outputs of this register are connected to the INITADDR outputs. The contents are incremented after each write to the INITWDATA register.

spirit:register.spirit:name: INITWDATA

spirit:field.spirit:name: INITDATA
spirit:field.spirit:description: Init/Config write data: If the parameter USE_INIT=1, these write-only bits are used to send initialization data out of the INITDATA[8:0] and INITDATVAL ports that may be connected to an instance of CoreABC configured to operate in soft mode. If the parameter USE_INIT=0, these bits are permanently tied to logic 0 and writes to it have no effect

spirit:register.spirit:description: Write-only access to INITCFG initialization address space (used to write to the INITDATA[8:0] inputs of CoreABC).

spirit:register.spirit:name: INITCTRL

spirit:field.spirit:name: INITDONE
spirit:field.spirit:description: Init/Config done bit: If the parameter USE_INIT=1, this bit controls the state of the INITDONE output pin to indicate that the initialization/configuration process is completed. This signal should only be set to logic 1 by processor A after it has completed writing all initialization data to the INIT* outputs that may be connected to an instance of CoreABC configured to operate in soft mode (this is accomplished by processor A writing to the INITWADDR and INITWDATA registers). If the INITWIDTH parameter is 0, this register bit is permanently tied to logic 0 and writes to it have no effect.

spirit:register.spirit:description: Control register to set or clear the INITDONE output signal

spirit:register.spirit:name: FIFOWDA2B

spirit:field.spirit:name: DATA
spirit:field.spirit:description: FIFO write data (width = MBX_WIDTH-1): During a write cycle, this data will be written from processor A into the A->B FIFO (for sending message data from processor A to processor B) if USE_FIFOS=1. If USE_FIFOS=0, writing to this address has no effect. This register is write-only.

spirit:register.spirit:description: Write-only access to send message from processor A to processor B. This address is only used if USE_FIFOS=1.

spirit:register.spirit:name: FIFORDB2A

spirit:field.spirit:name: DATA
spirit:field.spirit:description: FIFO read data (width = MBX_WIDTH-1): During a read cycle, this data will be read by processor A from the B->A FIFO (for sending message data from processor B to processor A) if USE_FIFOS=1. If USE_FIFOS=1, reading from this address has no effect (unknown logic values are returned and should be ignored). This register is read-only.

spirit:register.spirit:description: Read-only access to read message from processor B to processor A. This address is only used if USE_FIFOS=1.

spirit:register.spirit:name: DPRAMA

spirit:field.spirit:name: DATA
spirit:field.spirit:description: Refer to Handbook for description.

spirit:register.spirit:description: Processor A access to port A of internal dual-port SRAM instance(s) or optional ROM. This address space (0x2000 - 0x3FFC) is only used if USE_FIFOS=0.

spirit:field.spirit:name: EN_B_FLAGS_A2B_OR
spirit:field.spirit:description: Enable B_FLAGS_A2B_OR bit: This bit controls whether or not the ORed version of the flag bits from processor A to processor B (B_FLAGS_A2B[31:0]) contributes to the INTERRUPT_B output or is masked. If set to 1, the ORed flag contribution is enabled, otherwise, if 0, the ORed flag contribution is masked. The default value of 0 disables (masks) the contribution of the ORed flags to the INTERRUPT_B output.

spirit:field.spirit:name: EN_DPWRA
spirit:field.spirit:description: Enable DPWRA bit: This bit controls whether or not the DPWRA bit of the INTSTATB register contributes to the INTERRUPT_B output or is masked. If set to 1, the DPWRA bit contribution is enabled, otherwise, if 0, the DPWRA bit is masked. The default value of 0 disables (masks) the contribution of the DPWRA bit to the INTERRUPT_B output.

spirit:field.spirit:name: EN_FULL_B2A
spirit:field.spirit:description: Enable FULL_B2A bit: This bit controls whether or not the FULL_B2A bit of the INTSTATB register contributes to the INTERRUPT_B output or is masked. If set to 1, the FULL_B2A bit contribution is enabled, otherwise, if 0, the FULL_B2A bit is masked. The default value of 0 disables (masks) the contribution of the FULL_B2A bit to the INTERRUPT_B output.

spirit:field.spirit:name: EN_MSG_A2B
spirit:field.spirit:description: Enable MSG_A2B bit: This bit controls whether or not the MSG_A2B bit of the INTSTATB register contributes to the INTERRUPT_B output or is masked. If set to 1, the MSB_A2B bit contribution is enabled, otherwise, if 0, the MSG_A2B bit is masked. The default value of 0 disables (masks) the contribution of the MSG_A2B bit to the INTERRUPT_B output.

spirit:field.spirit:name: B_FLAGS_A2B_OR
spirit:field.spirit:description: ORed flag bits from processor A to processor B: If set to 1, this bit indicates that processor A has set one or more general purpose flags in the B_FLAGS_A2B[31:0] register to indicate to processor B that it must take some action followed by clearing of these general purpose flags; this action that must be taken by processor B is entirely application specific. This bit will not be cleared when reading this register, but rather when all bits of the B_FLAGS_A2B[31:0] register are cleared. If MSG_A2B_FLAGS=0, this bit will be permanently tied to logic 0.

spirit:field.spirit:name: DPWRA
spirit:field.spirit:description: Processor A has written to dual-port SRAM: If set to 1, this bit indicates that processor A has written data into the A port of the dual-port SRAM. This bit will be cleared when reading this register. If USE_FIFOS=1, this bit will be permanently tied to logic 0.

spirit:field.spirit:name: FULL_B2A
spirit:field.spirit:description: FIFO B->A is full: If set to 1, this bit indicates that the B->A FIFO (from processor B to processor A) is full. This bit will be cleared when at least one message has been read from the B->A FIFO by the A processor. If USE_FIFOS=0, this bit will be permanently tied to logic 0.

spirit:field.spirit:name: MSG_A2B
spirit:field.spirit:description: Message(s) available in FIFO A->B: If set to 1, this bit indicates that at least one message is available in the A->B FIFO (from processor A to processor B). This bit will be cleared when all messages have been read from the A->B FIFO. If USE_FIFOS=0, this bit will be permanently tied to logic 0.

spirit:register.spirit:name: B_FLAGS_B2A

spirit:field.spirit:name: FLAGS
spirit:field.spirit:description: Message flag bits from processor B to processor A: These 32 possible flag logic bits can be used to send interrupts from processor B to processor A. Processor B can set any of the 32 bits by writing a logic 1 in that bit position, for example, if the B_FLAGS_B2A[31:0] register value contains 0xFFAA0000 and processor B writes the value 0x00000055 to this register, the value will be changed to 0xFFAA0055 on subsequent reads since writing logic 0 values to any of the bits is ignored.

spirit:register.spirit:description: 32 possible flag logic bits that can be used to send interrupts from processor B to processor A (read-able and set-able from processor B).

spirit:register.spirit:name: B_FLAGS_A2B

spirit:field.spirit:name: FLAGS
spirit:field.spirit:description: Message flag bits from processor A to processor B: These 32 possible flag logic bits can be used to send interrupts from processor A to processor B. Processor B can clear any of the 32 bits by writing a logic 1 in that bit position, for example, if the B_FLAGS_A2B[31:0] register value contains 0x00550000 and processor B writes the value 0xFF55FFFF to this register, the value will be changed to 0x00000000 on subsequent reads; writing logic 0 values to any of the bits is ignored.

spirit:register.spirit:description: 32 possible flag logic bits that can be used to send interrupts from processor A to processor B (read-able and clear-able from processor B).

spirit:register.spirit:name: FIFORDA2B

spirit:field.spirit:name: DATA
spirit:field.spirit:description: FIFO read data (width = MBX_WIDTH-1): During a read cycle, this data will be read by processor B from the A->B FIFO (for sending message data from processor A to processor B) if USE_FIFOS=1. If USE_FIFOS=1, reading from this address has no effect (unknown logic values are returned and should be ignored). This register is read-only. Note that if PORT_B_WIDTH is less than MBX_WIDTH, then the number of data bits accessible from processor B will be limited to the value of PORT_B_WIDTH rather than the value of MBX_WIDTH.

spirit:register.spirit:description: Read-only access to read message from processor A to processor B. This address is only used if USE_FIFOS=1.

spirit:register.spirit:name: FIFOWDB2A

spirit:field.spirit:name: DATA
spirit:field.spirit:description: FIFO write data (width = MBX_WIDTH-1): During a write cycle, this data will be written from processor B into the B->A FIFO (for sending message data from processor B to processor A) if USE_FIFOS=1. If USE_FIFOS=0, writing to this address has no effect. This register is write-only. Note that if PORT_B_WIDTH is less than MBX_WIDTH, then the number of data bits accessible from processor B will be limited to the value of PORT_B_WIDTH rather than the value of MBX_WIDTH.

spirit:register.spirit:description: Write-only access to send message from processor B to processor A. This address is only used if USE_FIFOS=1.

spirit:register.spirit:name: DPRAMB

spirit:field.spirit:name: DATA
spirit:field.spirit:description: Refer to Handbook for description.

spirit:register.spirit:description: Processor B access to port B of internal dual-port SRAM instance(s) or optional ROM. This address space (0x2000 - 0x3FFC) is only used if USE_FIFOS=0.

spirit:vendorExtensions.actel-cc:description: CoreMBX (Mail Box) allows data messages (mail) to pass back and forth from one processing element to another. The user is able to choose (via CoreConsole or SmartDesign configuration) whether this message passing capability is implemented with one or more instances of dual-port SRAM hard macros or with one or more instances of FIFO hard macros.
